TASK_DESCRIPTION=RESEARCH TASK: Analyze ClawCode + oh-my-codex (OMX) + oh-my-opencode (OmO) ecosystem to identify best practices Doey should adopt. Full research material saved at .doey/tasks/attachments/task-490-clawcode-research.md — READ THIS FILE FIRST. Key areas to analyze against Doey's current architecture: (1) Event routing outside agent context (clawhip pattern) — how does Doey compare? (2) State-machine-first worker lifecycle vs Doey's current approach (3) Typed events vs prose/log scraping (4) Recovery-before-escalation patterns (5) Hash-anchored edit tool (Hashline) — 6.7% to 68.3% success rate improvement (6) The deep-interview → ralplan → team/ralph workflow pipeline (7) Skill-embedded MCPs — on-demand, scoped, context-clean (8) IntentGate for true intent analysis (9) Todo Enforcer — yanks idle agents back (10) Background agents — 5+ specialists in parallel with lean context (11) Agent category routing (visual/deep/quick/ultrabrain) instead of model picking. Deliverable: Prioritized findings report with concrete improvement proposals ranked by impact and effort.
